1.A switch can be attached with a call back to retrieve the value of the switch.


2.The state transition of a switch is from either ON to OFF or OFF to ON.



3.When switch makes any transition the callback is triggered and new state can be retrieved i.e came
and any other action can be taken based on the state.



4.By default, the representation of the widget is static. The minimum size required is 83*32 pixels.



5.The entire widget is active, not just the part with graphics. As long as you swipe over the widgetâ€™s
bounding box, it will work.